    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe `WinResized` event does not trigger when executing a lua script through neovim's commandline interface (via the `-l` flag).\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nExample file: `winresized.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\"WinResized\"}, {\r\n    callback = function ()\r\n        print(\"WinResized\")\r\n    end\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.wincmd('s')\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun: `nvim --clean -l winresized.lua`\r\n\r\nObserved Output: Nothing gets printed\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWe should see \"WinResized\" printed since the `winresized.lua` script created the autocmd to do so when the `WinResized` event occurs. The split command at the end of the script should have triggered the `WinResized` event.\r\n\r\nTo show a related example of how `WinResized` is supposed to work, here is the same thing with the `WinEnter` event (which does work):\r\n\r\nwinenter.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\"WinEnter\"}, {\r\n    callback = function ()\r\n        print(\"WinEnter\")\r\n    end\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.wincmd('s')\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun: `nvim --clean -l winenter.lua`\r\nOutput: \"WinEnter\" gets printed\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-1807+g096211a87\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nVim does not have the `WinResized` event\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nFedora\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
